    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Facilities that harness and distribute energy derived from the sun's radiation by producing heat, causing chemical reactions, or generating electricity in any of several methods, including but not limited to the following: by the using direct solar radiation to heat air, water, or another carrier fluid; by using arrays of lenses or mirrors as solar collectors to concentrate sunlight to produce high temperatures in a solar furnace; or by using solar cells (photovoltaic cells) to convert solar radiation into electricity when a small electric voltage is generated in the solar cell as light strikes the junction between a metal and a semiconductor (such as silicon) or the junction between two different semiconductors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>透過多種方式製造熱能、導致化學反應或產生電力，藉以利用並分配太陽輻射能量的設備。其中包括以下的方式：使用直接的太陽輻射來加熱空氣、水或其他運載流體(carrier fluid)。或利用一系列的透鏡或鏡子作為太陽能收集器，集中日光以在太陽爐(solar furnace)中產生高溫。或以太陽能電池，或稱光伏電池(photovoltaic cell)，將太陽輻射轉為電能，利用光線打到金屬和半導體(例如矽)之間，或打到兩個不同的半導體間時，在太陽能電池中產生小量的電壓。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
